column4: Wells Fargo mortgage buybacks could top $1.8 billion
column5: CHARLOTTE  North Carolina Wells Fargo & Co may have to buy back an additional $1.8 billion in toxic mortgages from outside investors on top of claims it already received  the fourth-largest U.S. bank by assets said in a securities filing on Friday.

column5: NEW YORK Wells Fargo & Co reached a $590 million deal to resolve a lawsuit alleging Wachovia misled investors about the quality of loans sold before the financial crisis  one of the largest settlements of its kind stemming from the housing market meltdown.
